§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A first square matrix is ❬similar❭ to a second square
    matrix if there exists a nonsingular matrix such that the
    first matrix is identical to the product of the inverse of
    the nonsingular matrix the second square matrix and the
    nonsingular matrix. ⦉
⦉

§ S Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $A, B ∈ 𝗥^{n × n}$. ⦉

  ‖ $B$ is similar to $A$ if there exists a nonsingular matrix
    $S ∈ 𝗥^{n × n}$ such that
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ B = S^{-1}AS. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

§ Equivalence Relation ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Similarity is an equivalence relation. ⦉
</statement>
